# Project Git Sync

Before making changes in this repository, apply the `project-git-sync` skill.

Required workflow:
- Run `git fetch origin`, then verify `git status --short`, `git status -sb`, `git rev-parse HEAD`, and `git rev-parse @{u}`.
- Only edit when the working tree is clean and local `HEAD` matches upstream.
- If changes or divergence exist, inspect and report them before editing.
- After each coherent task phase, validate, commit with a detailed message, and push before starting the next phase.
- Never commit `.env*`, credentials, tokens, or generated build output.
